summary: DT*: THE CONTACT STATED WHILE DRIVING 35 TO 40MPH ON AN ICE COVERED ROAD, THE VEHICLE'S FRONT TIRES DROPPED OFF THE SIDE OF THE ROAD, AND THIS CAUSED LOSS OF CONTROL OF THE VEHICLE.  THE VEHICLE WENT IN TO A DITCH, THIS WAS A FRONTAL IMPACT.  THE DRIVER'S SIDE AIRBAGS DID NOT DEPLOY.  THE SEAT BELTS WERE IN USE.  THE VEHICLE IS TOTALED.  THE MANUFACTURER HAS NOT BEEN ALERTED.
